
DANNY JOHNSON (AMERICAN FOOTBALL)
Danny Johnson (born November 17, 1995) is an American football cornerback for the Washington Redskins of the National Football League (NFL). He played college football at Southern University, and was signed by the Redskins as an undrafted free agent in 2018.
COLLEGE CAREER
Section::::College career.
Following his senior season, Johnson was invited to the 2018 Senior Bowl. He became the first Southern player to be invited to the senior bowl in 23 years.
PROFESSIONAL CAREER
Section::::Professional career.
Johnson participated in the 2018 NFL Combine. Johnson went unselected in the 2018 NFL Draft, but signed an undrafted free agent contract with the Washington Redskins soon after. He made his NFL debut in the Redskins' season opener against the Arizona Cardinals. He had a 24-yard kick return in the 24â€“6 victory. He was placed on injured reserve on December 19, 2018.
